Arrange a GInteractions by a column

Source: R/arrange.R
dplyr-arrange.Rd

Arrange a GInteractions by a column

Usage

# S3 method for GInteractions
arrange(.data, ...)

Arguments

.data

a GInteractions object

...

Variables, or functions of variables. Use dplyr::desc() to sort a variable in descending order.

Value

a GInteractions object.

Examples

gi <- read.table(text = "
chr1 1 10 chr1 1 10
chr1 2 10 chr2 1 10
chr3 3 10 chr3 1 10
chr4 4 10 chr4 1 10
chr5 5 10 chr5 1 10",
col.names = c("seqnames1", "start1", "end1", "seqnames2", "start2", "end2")) |> 
  as_ginteractions() |> 
  mutate(cis = seqnames1 == seqnames2, score = runif(5)*100, gc = runif(5))
gi
#> GInteractions object with 5 interactions and 3 metadata columns:

####################################################################
# 1. Arrange GInteractions by a numerical column
####################################################################
